7375175781648993568.voice_to_text: the mistakes Google's AI has been making has been related to their new feature AI Overview which was released in the US and due to release worldwide later in the year Google had hoped that this would be the future of the search engine but it admits that it had screwed up with regards to this new feature the company states that the mistakes were not hallucinations as the AI works differently to other chat bots instead they attributed the misleading results to information gaps where uncommon queries had less reliable sources for the AI to draw on for example drawing on satirical or unreliable websites for its answers Google has been making some changes for example is limiting the answers from the overviews to nonsensical questions and limiting the amount of humor and satire included in the overviews it's updated its systems to limit the amount of user generated content that would be used in the overviews that would potentially lead to misleading advice and it's launched additional refinements to enhance the quality in response to health related queries

7374916909814353195.voice_to_text: can you imagine being a history teacher today and teaching about the French Revolution and just no this was honestly my experience being a high school history teacher for the last 12 years and every year it got more and more surreal and more more difficult to keep a straight face there were so many lessons that I started to have to preface if you like I promise I haven't changed this in the 12 years I've been teaching like I promise I'm not trying to make a political point for example when I would teach about Watergate one Gen Z was like unfazed by Watergate they were like that was it was all he did broke in tried to wire tap some phones that's not that bad like they're so jaded about the state of our political system I think as they should be and then when I explained like Nixon fighting back and being like it's a witch hunt they're all out to get me like people thought like my students thought I was joking they thought I was putting stuff in to make little jabs at Trump and I was like no I genuinely just this is just what happened teaching about the revolutions went from being like oh the French Revolution is this fun silly thing that almost feels unreal to every year getting a little more and more real like every year when I would teach about the Gilded Age and like the titans of industry and we talked about Carnegie and Rockefeller and Vanderbilt all the kids would go like so like Zuckerberg and Bezos and Musk I’d be like I that's a really interesting connection

program is called Protego Health the Women's Optimal Health Framework and it is a program that has been developed in order to get countries in line with the Geneva Consensus Declaration or the GCD  now the GCD was formalized and launched in the last year of the Trump administration but its goals were to export anti LGBTQ policies and anti abortion policies around the world and Protego happens to be a tool for implementing those policies now the GCD was initially signed by 32 countries but after elections in Brazil and Colombian in the United States more left leaning leaders have withdrawn their countries from this declaration the GCD claims to do four things it has four pillars  it's improving women's health protecting human life strengthening the family  and protecting each country's national sovereignty to "support their own core values" however these pillars are a smoke screen the main goal of the GCD is to strip countries of development aid if they are providing their people If he succeeds, that war is also made it all too clear the risk to our energy security. In the Middle East, the forces of Islamist extremism threatened regional and ultimately global stability. According to Ukrainian media, Ukraine is currently facing shortages not only in ammunition, but also in qualified personnel. The video reveals that Volkarov, under the taunting of veteran soldiers, was instructed to operate a mortar. Unfortunately, he loaded the shell incorrectly, almost leading to a catastrophe. Afterward, unaware of his mistake, Volkarov was verbally and physically abused by the veterans, leaving him terrified and crying in the trench. War is brutal, and even for able bodied soldiers the survival rate on the front lines is low. For someone like Vokerov, who has down syndrome, escaping a tragic fate is even more unlikely. Sent to the front lines despite being unable to care for himself, Volkarov stands little chance of participating in combat and risks becoming cannon fodder. Rumors suggest that his comrades even considered using Volkarov to attract Russian drones, and one Ukrainian veteran reportedly wanted him to test for landmines. Vokorov's case has brought public attention and concern to the treatment of vulnerable soldiers within the Ukrainian military. Some Ukrainians hope that Russian forces will capture Vokorov, believing it might save him from further suffering.

7369287789030182190.video_description: A pod of orcas sunk a yacht a few miles from the Strait of Gibraltar early Sunday. THe same pod of orcas has been toying with boats since 2020. #TODAYShow #Orcas
7369287789030182190.voice_to_text: It’s the kind of heart-stopping  wildlife encounter sailors dread. Killer whales ramming boats, at times breaking the rudders leaving the boats unsteerable or worse, sinking them. And now it's happened again. The crew of the 50-foot Alberon Coñac sailboat calling for help early Sunday, a few miles from the Strait of Gibraltar  in Moroccan waters, saying orcas damaged the rudder  and the yacht was taking on water. The crew rescued, the boat sank. The same pod of orcas have been toying with boats off the  Atlantic coast of Spain, Portugal, and France since 2020. More than 400 encounters sinking  at least five boats. This particular pod is critically endangered and scientists say returns to the same  area every year looking for bluefin tuna. Marine conservation group  Ocean Care stressing “We do not believe that the orcas’  behaviour is any form of revenge or a deliberate attack on people.” Experts think the orcas may actually be  teaching each other how to break boat rudders. Spanish Maritime Rescue now telling sailors to steer clear of the area  from April to August, stay close to the coast,  and don't try to harm the animals.

7368414721596230917.video_description: Hmm bakalan naik nggak ya? Presiden Jokowi akan menghapus sistem kelas 1, 2, dan 3 di BPJS Kesehatan. Sebagai gantinya, seluruh rumah sakit wajib menerapkan Kelas Rawat Inap Standar (KRIS) paling lambat 30 Juni 2025. Iuran BPJS Kesehatan selama ini dibedakan sesuai kelasnya, yakni untuk Kelas III Rp 42.000 per bulan. Tapi per 1 Januari 2021 dapat subsidi pemerintah Rp 7.000, jadi hanya Rp 35.000 per bulan. Kemudian Kelas II Rp 100.000 per bulan dan Kelas I Rp 150.000 per bulan. Direktur Keuangan dan Investasi BPJS Kesehatan, Arief Witjaksono Juwono, mengatakan untuk penggolongan iuran program Jaminan Kesehatan Nasional (JKN) BPJS Kesehatan dengan format baru nantinya menunggu keputusan pemerintah. “Kita menunggu dari pemerintah bagaimana apakah konsekuensi single class itu nanti single iuran, kita belum tahu. Ini masih berprogres,” kata Arief saat ditemui di Masjid At Tanwir PP Muhammadiyah, Jakarta, Senin (13/5). 📸: Dok. kumparan/Akbar Maulana. #bisnisupdate #update #bisnis #svt #bpjs #jokowi #iuran #kris #info #infoterkini #berita #beritaterkini #kumparan #tiktokberita

7368336425093238021.video_description: Pimpinan Pondok Pesantren (Ponpes) NQW di Lombok berinisial MA diduga melecehkan lima santriwatinya. Kasus ini sudah dilaporkan ke Polres Lombok Barat. Ketua Lembaga Perlindungan Anak (LPA) Kota Mataram, Joko Jumadi, yang mendampingi para korban, MA membantah sebagai pelaku pelecehan terhadap lima orang santriwati. MA malah berdalih hal itu dilakukan oleh makhluk gaib. Pernyataan MA tersebut diperoleh LPA Kota Mataram dari keterangan orang tua korban dan santriwati yang mendapat pelecehan seksual. Mereka semua sempat dipertemukan dengan Pimpinan Ponpes NQW oleh tokoh masyarakat di Desa Persiapan Pesisir Mas, Kecamatan Sekotong, Lombok Barat, Nusa Tenggara Barat (NTB). "Menurut cerita dari orang tua korban kemudian juga oleh korban yang sempat dipertemukan oleh tokoh masyarakat. Dalam pertemuan tersebut, MA tidak mengakui perbuatannya tapi mengatakan yang melakukannya makhluk gaib," kata Joko kepada wartawan di Mataram, Minggu (12/5). 📸: Dok. Polres Lombok Barat. #newsupdate #update #news #videonews #ponpes #pesantren #santriwati #info #infoterkini #beritaterkini #kumparan

7368089174810823944.video_description: AKA (13) seorang santri di Lamongan dianiaya oleh tiga temannya. Korban yang merupakan laki-laki itu diikat lalu diangkat oleh temannya. AKA terjatuh hingga terluka di telinga.⁠ ⁠ Peristiwa itu terjadi di Ponpes Matholiul Anwar Jalan Raya Simo, Desa Sungelebak, Kecamatan Karanggeneng, Kabupaten Lamongan, pada Minggu (5/5) sekitar pukul 21.00 WIB.⁠ ⁠ "Ketiga santri dan juga korban yang bersangkutan sudah ditanyai. Jadi, kejadian tersebut bisa terjadi disebabkan lantaran guyonan (bercanda)," papar pengurus Ponpes Matholi'ul Anwar, Abdulloh Faqih, Minggu (12/5).⁠ ⁠ "Dia diikat itu benar. Tapi, kalau dibanting sampai tak sadarkan diri itu tidak benar. Posisinya korban ini diangkat bertiga, lalu jatuh begitu saja," terang Faqih. Setelah kejadian itu korban didampingi pembina dibawa ke klinik dan pihak klinik mengatakan korban tidak apa-apa. Saat ini, polisi masih melakukan pendalaman terkait penganiayaan tersebut.⁠ ⁠ 📸: Dok. mili.id, Shutterstock/Ilustrasi.⁠ ⁠ #focus #santrilamongan #news #videonews #santri #lamongan #ponpes #pondokpesantren #info #infoterkini #berita #beritaterkini #kumparan

7364443869238299947.video_description: President Biden on Thursday condemned protests on college campuses that have turned violent or hateful, saying “there’s the right to protest, but not the right to cause chaos.”   “Peaceful protest is in the best tradition of how Americans respond to consequential issues, but neither are we a lawless country,” he said in remarks from the White House. “We are a civil society and order must prevail.”   The president’s message came as pro-Palestinian demonstrations and counterprotests have roiled campuses throughout the country. Students have set up encampments and issued demands that schools divest from Israel. On many campuses, police have been called in to respond to violence and property destruction.   “Destroying property is not a peaceful protest — it’s against the law,” he said. “Vandalism, trespassing, breaking windows, shutting down campuses, forcing the cancelation of classes and graduations — none of this is a peaceful protest.”   President Biden said “dissent is essential to democracy” but that dissent must not turn in lawlessness or bigotry.   “There should be no place on any campus, no place in America, for antisemitism or threats of violence against Jewish students,” he said. “There is no place for hate speech or violence of any kind whether it’s antisemitism, Islamophobia, or discrimination against Arab Americans or Palestinian Americans. It’s simply wrong.”   Responding to reporters’ questions, the president said the protests have not made him reconsider any policies with respect to the war in Gaza.   He also said “no” when asked whether the National Guard should be deployed to campuses to quell the demonstrations.” #potus #joebiden #protests #gazawar #israelhamaswar #cspan

7364410606184647969.video_description: Antony Blinken says there is currently a ceasefire proposal “on the table” US Secretary of State Antony Blinken said the US is “determined” to achieve a hostage exchange and ceasefire deal “now” during his visit to Tel Aviv on Wednesday. Blinken arrived in Israel on Tuesday for talks with Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu and other officials following visits to Jordan and Saudi Arabia, his seventh trip to the region since the beginning of Israel’s offensive on Gaza. Speaking jointly to reporters during the visit, Israeli President Isaac Herzog urged Israel’s "allies and friends" to reject efforts by the International Criminal Court (ICC) taken against the country for its war on Gaza. Herzog characterised the reported ICC investigation into Israeli leaders as a "clear and present danger to democracies and to free and peace-loving nations, who pursue the norms of international law". Recently, several senior Israeli officials have voiced concern over the ICC's investigation into Israel’s actions in Gaza and the occupied West Bank. Reports suggest that the court could issue arrest warrants for Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu and other Israeli leaders. Israel’s war on Gaza has killed over 34,500 Palestinians since 7 October 2023, the majority being women and children.

7354493993964539178.video_description: Could your favorite artist's streams be skyrocketing because of fake plays? Spotify thinks so. Here's how streaming farms like these have taken over charts and shut out smaller artists. #Reacts #streaming #musicindustry #streams #billboardcharts
7354493993964539178.voice_to_text: This is what a streaming farm looks like, aka the black market of the music industry. It's how some musicians and labels distort reality to push their tracks to the top of the charts and earn more money. Streaming farms use bots to artificially play music on platforms like Spotify or Apple Music to drastically inflate the numbers of streams a song gets. In March, a man in Denmark was sentenced to 18 months in prison for getting music streaming services to pay him $290,000 in royalties for fake streams. But that rare case is just a glimpse into the scale of this fraud. In 2,019 Rolling Stone article, Hopeless Records founder Louis Posin claimed this illegal practice potentially steals $300 million a year from artists with legitimate streams from real fans, equaling 3 to 4% of all streams. But that estimate is much higher now. A 2023 analyst report from the Financial Times found that up to 10% of all music streams globally are fake. Matters because there's a pool of money that streaming platforms distribute to the rights holders of songs. So when an artist is faking those dreams, they're taking money out of that pool could go to artists with legitimate streams. The creation of streaming farms follows the decline of radio and the rise of its replacement streaming platforms. Major artists and labels historically paid radio DJs to play their music. But streaming platforms like Spotify are democratizing music, allowing independent artists a platform. But that means Larger artists and labels are struggling to stay on top of the charts, so they compete by buying streams. Streaming services like Spotify have recently tried to crack down on this by looking specifically for erratic behavior like a sudden jumping streams or song on repeat for hours. A Spotify spokesperson said that when they detect artificial streams, they withhold royalties and tell the labeler distributor. They can also choose to remove tracks from the platform and find labels in distributor, but some musicians say they're being targeted by bots and then unfairly punished as a result. Marketing agencies hired by the artist might be responsible though, going behind the backs of the artist to fulfill their promises. Apple Music has similarly been penalizing streaming fraud 2 since 2022, but somehow people are continuing to steal from the royalty pool, which is already too small and meant for artists with real fans. And with advancements in AI, who knows what the scale of this issue could actually be now and in the future.
